                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JAMES SQUIRES. I live with a tailor in New Kent-road. On the 2d of March, between three and four o'clock; I was looking at the ruins of the <placeName id="t18280410-190-crimeloc1019">Brunswick Theatre</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-190-crimeloc1019" type="placeName" value="Brunswick Theatre"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-190-crimeloc1019" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-190-off1017 t18280410-190-crimeloc1019"></join>; there were a great many people there; I felt the prisoner's hand coming out of my waistcoat pocket, where I had this money; I caught hold of him, and asked him for my money: the officer got it from him. I lost a half-crown, a shilling, and two farthings: the shilling dropped; I took it up, and gave it to the officer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-190-person1083">
                  HENRY 
                  HILLIER
               <interp inst="t18280410-190-person1083" type="surname" value="HILLIER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-190-person1083" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-190-person1083" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was at the ruins of the Theatre, and saw the prosecutor there; he accused the prisoner, who was close to him, of stealing his money - I saw the prisoner put his hand behind him, and put some money into his coat pocket; I could not see what but something dropped.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-190-person1084">
                  THOMAS 
                  JOSEPH WEST
               <interp inst="t18280410-190-person1084" type="surname" value="JOSEPH WEST"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-190-person1084" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-190-person1084" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I took the prisoner, and found a half-crown in his pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-190-person1085">
                  JAMES 
                  GLEDBURY
               <interp inst="t18280410-190-person1085" type="surname" value="GLEDBURY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-190-person1085" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-190-person1085" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw the prisoner attempt several pockets before he went up to Squires - I went up, seeing a scuffle - Squires picked up a shilling and a farthing, and gave them to me.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had this half-crown and three halfpence in my pocket - this gentleman put his hand into his pocket, he let his money fall, and charged me with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280410-190-verdict1020" type="verdictDescription">
